    "Additionally, by analyzing the 2-norm of output token embeddings (mean 1.52, SD 0.23), we find that the latter also approximately lie on a sphere, of radius 1.52.",
    "Token energy.",
    "Importantly, token embeddings occupy their sphere unevenly; e.g., the first 25% of the principal components account for 50% of the total variance, and the first 54% for 80%.",
    "2 To build intuition, first consider a hypothetical extreme case where tokens lie in a proper subspace (\"token subspace\") of the full d-dimensional space (even though, empirically, U has rank d, so the tokens' output embeddings span all of R d).",
    "If a latent h has a component orthogonal to the token subspace, it includes information that is irrelevant for predicting the next token based on h alone (since logits are scalar products of latent and token vectors)."
